oke a static method.\\n\\nBut using `InvokerHelper` directly in a generated class might complicate things a bit. I wonder if I can generate the class using temporary javac while still ensuring it refers to the class literal and `InvokerHelper`. That could be a good workaround!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_lazC8m37oAhrLlyMIEKS82Ga|fc_022dadbd019744ed016a0180f1e6b48192b6a794138166a0dc", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/src/test/java/io/restassured/internal/ResponseSpecificationImplHeaderClosure7Access.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage io.restassured.internal;\n\nimport org.codehaus.groovy.runtime.InvokerHelper;\n\npublic final class ResponseSpecificationImplHeaderClosure7Access {\n    private ResponseSpecificationImplHeaderClosure7Access() {\n    }\n\n    public static Class<?> activeClosureClass() {\n        return ResponseSpecificationImpl$_header_closure7.class;\n    }\n\n    public static Object invokeClassResolverThroughGroovyDispatch(String className) {\n        return InvokerHelper.invokeStaticMethod(activeClosureClass(), \"class$\", new Object[] {className});\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1010, "output": 2001, "cacheRead": 76800, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 79811, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778483409435, "responseId": "resp_022dadbd019744ed016a0180d22c6881928186c96d9da1f69b"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_lazC8m37oAhrLlyMIEKS82Ga|fc_022dadbd019744ed016a0180f1e6b48192b6a794138166a0dc", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 747 bytes to tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest